## Folder structure
```
.
├── public/
│   └── images/               # SVG placeholder image slots (text-only PR safe)
├── src/
│   ├── components/           # reusable UI blocks
│   ├── data/                 # editable copy/content and schema helpers
│   ├── layouts/              # page wrapper layout + lightweight animation script
│   ├── pages/                # all routes
│   └── styles/               # global design system CSS
├── astro.config.mjs
├── package.json
└── REDESIGN_NOTES.md
```

## Stable image system (no broken remote URLs)
To avoid broken image icons on Vercel, the site now uses **stable local SVG visuals** from `/public/images/`.
No binary image files are committed.

### Active visual sources
All image references are mapped through `src/data/images.ts` and point to local SVG files:
- Hero visual
- Hydroseeding service visual
- Lawn installation visual
- Commercial erosion control visual
- New construction lawn visual
- Lawn maintenance visual
- Soil prep visual
- Before/after gallery visuals
- Contact/quote visual

### Reliability + fallback behavior
- Images use local SVG paths (no dynamic topic URLs).
- `ImageFrame` includes on-error fallback handling so broken image icons are hidden.
- Premium gradient/texture overlays and badges remain visible even if an image fails.

### Important usage warning
- These are representative demo visuals only.
- Do **not** represent them as real Hydroseed Inc. project photos.

### How to replace with real client photos later
1. Upload approved images to `/public/images/` or your CDN.
2. Update `src/data/images.ts` with the new stable URLs.
3. Keep alt text accurate and transparent.
4. Keep captions factual (no unverified project claims).

### Current local visual filenames
- `hero-hydroseeding.svg`
- `large-lawn-installation.svg`
