## Animation system
- Scroll reveal (`[data-reveal]`) using IntersectionObserver.
- Staggered child reveal (`data-reveal="stagger"`) for cards.
- Subtle parallax shift for hero visual groups (`[data-parallax]`).
- Sticky desktop quote prompt toggled after scroll.

No heavy animation libraries are used.

## SEO improvements included
- Unique page titles and descriptions.
- Semantic heading structure.
- Local-intent internal links between service and location pages.
- FAQ content on homepage and detail pages.
- JSON-LD support for LocalBusiness, Service, and FAQPage.
- Sitemap route (`/sitemap.xml`) and robots route (`/robots.txt`).
- Natural keyword integration (no stuffing).

## Quote form integration options (currently frontend-only)
The form is intentionally backend-free in this demo. You can connect it via:

### Netlify Forms
- Add `name="quote"` and `data-netlify="true"` on `<form>`.
- Include hidden `<input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="quote" />`.

### Formspree
- Set `action="https://formspree.io/f/{your-id}"` and `method="POST"`.

### EmailJS
- Add client-side script with EmailJS SDK and map fields to template variables.

### Resend or custom API route
- Add server endpoint (Astro API route) and send validated payload to email service.

## Install and run
> If your environment blocks npm registry access, install commands will fail until network policy is updated.

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

## Build
```bash
npm run build
npm run preview
```

## Deploy
### Vercel
1. Push repo to GitHub.
2. Import project in Vercel.
3. Build command: `npm run build`
4. Output directory: `dist`

### Replit
1. Import repo into Replit.
2. Run `npm install`.
3. Run: `npm run dev -- --host`

## Respectful outreach framing (Tobin Studio)
- Frame this as a growth-ready redesign demo, not a teardown.
- Acknowledge existing site strengths first.
- Highlight improved lead clarity, trust presentation, and local SEO structure.
- Replace placeholders with real media, approved reviews, and owner-verified details before launch.
